  "text": "By combining insight gained from Eqn. 8 with the definition of noise as a stochastic process [Lagae et al. 2010a, Sec. 2 .2], we were able to generalize the Fourier Slice Theorem as used by [CITATION_1] . More specifically, we generalize from a single noise instance and its Fourier transform to the stochastic process corresponding to the noise and its power spectrum.",
